  <p>
    If you want to make a fake chat — a screenshot for a meme or demo, or an animated "texting story" video for TikTok — three names come up a lot: <strong>TextingStory</strong>, <strong>Easy Chat Maker</strong> and <strong>Zeoob</strong>. They overlap, but they're built for different things. Here's an honest breakdown of what each one is best at, so you can pick the right one instead of installing all three.
  </p>

  <p>
    Full disclosure: this is published by Easy Chat Maker, so treat our own entry with healthy skepticism. We've tried to keep the comparison fair — the other two are genuinely good at what they do. Features and pricing change, so check each tool's current terms before you commit.
  </p>

  <h2>The short version</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>TextingStory</strong> — a polished mobile app that pioneered the texting-story <em>video</em> format. Best if you want a native app experience and don't mind a watermark (or paying to remove it).</li>
    <li><strong>Zeoob</strong> — a long-running web tool for fake social posts and chat <em>screenshots</em> across many networks. Best for one-off static screenshots of a specific platform.</li>
    <li><strong>Easy Chat Maker</strong> — a free web tool that does both screenshots <em>and</em> videos across 9 platforms (including AI chats), with no watermark. Best if you want one tool for everything without paying or signing up.</li>
  </ul>

